        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8422",
        "content": "But to morrow I will take him prisoner and lead him away dejected and abject.\" Then they slept till daybreak, when the battle drums beat to fight and the swords in baldric were dight; and war cries were cried amain and all mounted their horses of generous strain and drew out into the field, filling every wide place and hill and plain.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-low_s-slow_e-low",
