        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8422",
        "content": "When it was the Six Hundred and Sixty sixth Night,",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-low_s-slow_e-high",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "very low",
        "speed": "slow",
        "energy": "high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8422_258259_000005_000008",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8422/258259/8422_258259_000005_000008.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8422",
        "content": "Then he went in to Mahdiyah and took her maidenhead and abode with her ten days; after which he committed the kingdom to his uncle Al Damigh, charging him to rule the lieges justly, and journeyed with his women and warriors, till he came to the ships laden with the treasures and rarities which Ra'ad Shah had sent him, and divided the monies among his men who from poor became rich.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-low_s-slow_e-low",
